  "prompt": "I just got friendzoned. What should I do now?",
  "response": "Getting friendzoned can be tough, but it\u2019s important to handle it with grace and self-respect. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: It\u2019s okay to feel disappointed or hurt. Give yourself permission to process your emotions without judgment.\n\n2. **Respect Their Boundaries**: If the other person has made it clear they see you as a friend, respect their feelings and avoid pressuring them. Trying to push the situation could strain the relationship.\n\n3. **Communicate Honestly (If Needed)**: If you feel the need to express your feelings, do so calmly and respectfully. Let them know how you feel, but also acknowledge their perspective. This can help bring closure.\n\n4. **Reevaluate the Relationship**: Decide if you\u2019re comfortable staying friends. If being around them feels too painful or one-sided, it\u2019s okay to take some space for yourself.\n\n5. **Focus on Yourself**: Use this time to invest in your own growth, hobbies, and well-being. Surround yourself with supportive friends and activities that make you happy.\n\n6. **Stay Open to New Opportunities**: Don\u2019t let this experience close you off to future relationships. There are plenty of people out there who might be a better match for you.\n\n7. **Learn from the Experience**: Reflect on what you\u2019ve learned about yourself, your needs, and what you\u2019re looking for in a relationship. This can help you grow and approach future connections with clarity.\n\nRemember, being friendzoned doesn\u2019t diminish your worth. It\u2019s just a step in your journey toward finding the right connection. Keep your head up and move forward with confidence!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
